snippets.title: DatasetService importFeatureValues Sample
snippets.description: Imports Feature values into the Featurestore from a source storage. The progress of the import is tracked by the returned operation. The imported features are guaranteed to be visible to subsequent read operations after the operation is marked as successfully done. If an import operation fails, the Feature values returned from reads and exports may be inconsistent. If consistency is required, the caller must retry the same import request again and wait till the new operation returned is marked as successfully done. There are also scenarios where the caller can cause inconsistency.  - Source data for import contains multiple distinct Feature values for    the same entity ID and timestamp.  - Source is modified during an import. This includes adding, updating, or  removing source data and/or metadata. Examples of updating metadata  include but are not limited to changing storage location, storage class,  or retention policy.  - Online serving cluster is under-provisioned.

snippets.title: DatasetService batchReadFeatureValues Sample
snippets.description: Batch reads Feature values from a Featurestore. This API enables batch reading Feature values, where each read instance in the batch may read Feature values of entities from one or more EntityTypes. Point-in-time correctness is guaranteed for Feature values of each read instance as of each instance's read timestamp.

snippets.title: DatasetService deleteFeatureValues Sample
snippets.description: Delete Feature values from Featurestore. The progress of the deletion is tracked by the returned operation. The deleted feature values are guaranteed to be invisible to subsequent read operations after the operation is marked as successfully done. If a delete feature values operation fails, the feature values returned from reads and exports may be inconsistent. If consistency is required, the caller must retry the same delete request again and wait till the new operation returned is marked as successfully done.

snippets.title: DatasetService suggestTrials Sample
snippets.description: Adds one or more Trials to a Study, with parameter values suggested by Vertex AI Vizier. Returns a long-running operation associated with the generation of Trial suggestions. When this long-running operation succeeds, it will contain a [SuggestTrialsResponse][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.SuggestTrialsResponse].

snippets.title: DatasetService createTrial Sample
snippets.description: Adds a user provided Trial to a Study.

snippets.title: DatasetService listTrials Sample
snippets.description: Lists the Trials associated with a Study.

snippets.title: DatasetService addTrialMeasurement Sample
snippets.description: Adds a measurement of the objective metrics to a Trial. This measurement is assumed to have been taken before the Trial is complete.

snippets.title: DatasetService checkTrialEarlyStoppingState Sample
snippets.description: Checks  whether a Trial should stop or not. Returns a long-running operation. When the operation is successful, it will contain a [CheckTrialEarlyStoppingStateResponse][google.cloud.aiplatform.v1.CheckTrialEarlyStoppingStateResponse].

snippets.title: DatasetService listOptimalTrials Sample
snippets.description: Lists the pareto-optimal Trials for multi-objective Study or the optimal Trials for single-objective Study. The definition of pareto-optimal can be checked in wiki page. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pareto_efficiency
